main event: Numerous witnesses reported seeing a luminous object in the sky near Winona, Mississippi between April 16-19, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as larger than a star or planet and displayed sudden changes in direction and altitude,The witness Mr. E. G. Brock, a retired Air Force colonel, reported seeing the object which pulsated in brightness,The object appeared to be about 5 to 10 miles away at an estimated altitude of 2000 to 3000 feet,The sightings included a strong odor of gasoline in the area where the object hovered,The observation lasted for about 10 minutes and there was no sound associated with the object.
witness description: Mr. E. G. Brock, a retired colonel in the U.S. Air Force
